title: U.S. stock futures gain after Trump signs coronavirus relief package

title: Trump signs bipartisan coronavirus relief bill after calling on Congress to approve $2,000 stimulus checks
text: President Donald Trump has signed the $900 billion coronavirus relief package on Sunday after earlier threatening to reject it because it didn't have larger stimulus payments. "I will sign the Omnibus and Covid package with a strong message that makes clear to Congress that wasteful items need to be removed," Trump said in a statement. "I will send back to Congress a redlined version, item by item, accompanied by the formal rescission request to Congress insisting that those funds be removed from the bill."

title: Donald Trump Signs Covid-19 Relief And Government Funding Bill
text: President Donald Trump signed a massive $2.3 trillion Covid-19 relief and government funding bill, ending several days of Christmas season drama as he balked at the legislation. title: Trump signs Covid relief and government funding bill days after he suggested he would block it
text: President Donald Trump signed a massive coronavirus relief and government funding package into law Sunday, days after he sent Washington into a panic by suggesting he could veto the bill.

title: Trump signs stimulus bill ahead of government shutdown, releasing checks and aid
text: After days of refusing to sign the stimulus bill into law, Trump has now authorized the joint COVID-19 relief aid and government funding bill.

title: Trump signs pandemic aid and spending bill, source says
text: U.S. President Donald Trump on Sunday signed into law a $2.3 trillion pandemic aid and spending package, restoring unemployment benefits to millions of Americans and averting a partial federal government shutdown, a source familiar with the matter said.
